dadamachines TBD-16 / CTAG TBD

TBD "to be determined" is an open-source platform for audio DSP experimentation,
learning, and research, bringing together high-quality generators and effects
within a modular, easily extensible architecture.

This repository is a fork of the CTAG TBD project, conceived within the
Creative Technologies Arbeitsgruppe of Kiel University of Applied Sciences:
https://www.creative-technologies.de

The core platform and original hardware designs were developed by Robert Manzke
(CTAG Kiel). The TBD-16 standalone hardware, the macro/preset/rack layer, the
WebUI, the REST API, documentation and the broader TBD-16 software layer were
developed by dadamachines — Johannes Elias Lohbihler — together with
Per-Olov Jernberg (possan, https://possan.codes), who authored the macro/preset
system and the rack layer.

(c) 2020-2026 Robert Manzke. All rights reserved. (core platform / engine, original hardware research)
(c) 2014-2026 Johannes Elias Lohbihler for dadamachines. (TBD-16 adaptation, REST API, WebUI, documentation)
(c) 2025-2026 Per-Olov Jernberg (possan). https://possan.codes (macro/preset system, rack layer)

Per-file copyright notices and any submodule licences take precedence over the
summary below where they differ.


