THE WebUI — NOT under the GPL
-----------------------------
The dadamachines TBD-16 WebUI under sdcard_image/www/ (the dadamachines-authored
HTML, JavaScript and CSS — index.html, the *.js application files, app.css, the
preset/macro manager, the WebUI updater, etc.) is:

  (c) 2014-2026 dadamachines / Johannes Elias Lohbihler. All rights reserved.

It is NOT licensed under the GPL or any other open-source licence. It is a
separate program that communicates with the TBD-16 firmware over the firmware's
REST API; it is not a derivative work of the firmware. You may not copy, modify,
redistribute or reuse the WebUI without dadamachines' written permission.
Vendored web components bundled with it (Shoelace, webaudio-controls, Sortable,
the Shoelace theme CSS, …) keep their own licences — see THIRD-PARTY.md.
Licensing enquiries: https://dadamachines.com/contact/


HARDWARE DESIGNS
----------------
The original CTAG TBD Eurorack hardware designs by Robert Manzke (V1/V2) are
released under the Creative Commons Attribution-NonCommercial-ShareAlike 4.0
International (CC BY-NC-SA 4.0).
Details here: https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/4.0/

The dadamachines TBD-16 (desktop instrument) and TBD-Core (core DSP board for
custom products) are commercial products. Their hardware designs are proprietary
and not released under an open-source licence.

An open-hardware core design based on the same ESP32-P4 + RP2350 platform is
planned for future publication in KiCad as an open-source reference, to foster
education, prototyping, and instrument design.


